article.headline: S. Illinois 33, Indiana St. 0
article.story: TERRE HAUTE, Ind. -- Redshirt freshman quarterback Paul McIntosh rushed for two touchdowns in his first start to pace Southern Illinois to a 33-0 shutout of Indiana State on Saturday. McIntosh replaced Chris Dieker, who is expected to miss six weeks with a broken collarbone. McIntosh, a transfer from Army, ran it in twice from 2 yards out. He also completed 15 of 22 passes for 159 yards. Deji Karim rushed 15 times for 87 yards and a touchdown in SIU's seventh straight victory. The Salukis (7-1, 6-0 Missouri Valley) also scored on Kyle Dougherty's field goal, a blocked punt and a safety. Antoine Brown ran 18 times for 36 yards for the Sycamores (1-8, 1-5). Southern Illinois outgained Indiana State 360 yards to 90.
